criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients treated three times per week with HD for at least 3 months and up to 24
             months;

          -  Clinically stable according to the evaluation of the investigator;

          -  Kt/V of > 1.2;

          -  Patients with an arteriovenous fistula/graft and permanent catheters with adequate
             flow.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age below 18 years;

          -  Life expectancy less than 3 months because of nonrenal disease;

          -  Participation in another clinical intervention trial;

          -  Severe non-compliance regarding frequency and duration of dialysis treatment;

          -  Patients with severe limitation to mobility (amputated, neurologic and muscular
             disorders) will be excluded from the study.
